  "text": "Both immunoblots and the impermeant CA inhibitor indicated the bulk of CA was intracellular. Some inhibition did occur with the impermeable QAS suggesting that about one-fourth of the total CA activity is extracellular. A possible scheme for CA-facilitated S i reabsorption should perhaps involve intracellular CAII dehydroxylation of HCO [CITATION_1] Ϫ that enters the cell in exchange for S i across the BLM by S i /HCO 3 Ϫ exchange thus sustaining a local HCO [CITATION_2] Ϫ gradient for S i exit to the interstitium.",
